      SDVariable SDLoss.softmaxCrossEntropy(SDVariable oneHotLabels, SDVariable logitPredictions, SDVariable weights, LossReduce lossReduce, double labelSmoothing)
      Applies the softmax activation function to the input, then implement multi-class cross entropy:
      -sum_classes label[i] * log(p[c]) where p = softmax(logits)
      If NONE is used, returned shape is [numExamples] out for [numExamples, numClasses] predicitons/labels;
      otherwise, the output is a scalar.
      SDVariable SDLoss.softmaxCrossEntropy(String name, SDVariable oneHotLabels, SDVariable logitPredictions, SDVariable weights, LossReduce lossReduce, double labelSmoothing)

      otherwise, the output is a scalar.
